definition:
A man of the tribe of Reuben living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.16.1; 
 son of: Eliab (H0446H); 
 brother of: Abiram (H0048) and Nemuel (H5241) 
 § Dathan = "belonging to a fountain"
 a Reubenite chief, son of Eliab, who, with his brother, Abiram, joined Korah's conspiracy against Moses' authority
